sec.p:
I now introduce an interesting corporate strategy for commodities. The Dow Chemical Company, a huge petrochemical company, has been successful in the commodities field. The outline of its strategy is as follows:
Keep the top share, or continue securing the share within the top three;
Maintain superiority, even if differences with other companies in terms of quality and manufacturing cost are actually small;
To achieve the above, continue investing no matter how bad the economic environment is;
On top of that, it is important to make a society that is not afraid of failure.
